50|$|Moimoi or Moin-Moin is a Nigerian steamed bean pudding {{made from}} a mixture of washed and peeled black-eyed peas, onions and fresh <b>ground</b> <b>peppers</b> (usually a {{combination}} of bell peppers and chili or scotch bonnet). It is a protein-rich food that is a staple in Nigeria. Some adaptations also put apples in MoiMoi. It originated from West Africa.|$|R
