5000|$|Perico (or huevos pericos, lit. [...] "parrot eggs") is a dish in Venezuelan cuisine {{prepared}} with scrambled eggs, butter, sautéed diced onions, and tomatoes. Scallions are a frequent substitution or {{addition to the}} onions, especially in Colombia. Perico may also include chopped cilantro greens, <b>ground</b> <b>peppers,</b> annatto and occasionally hot peppers. It {{can be regarded as}} a tropical version of scrambled eggs and can be eaten alone, with bread, usually at breakfast time; or at any time, as an arepa filling.|$|R
